<sect2 role="package"><title/>
<para>Le paquet Sed contient un éditeur de flux.</para>

<segmentedlist>
<segtitle>&buildtime;</segtitle>
<segtitle>&diskspace;</segtitle>
<seglistitem><seg>0,2&nbsp;SBU</seg><seg>8,4&nbsp;Mo</seg></seglistitem>
</segmentedlist>

<segmentedlist>
<segtitle>&dependencies;</segtitle>
<seglistitem><seg>Bash, Binutils, Coreutils,
Diffutils, GCC, Gettext, Glibc, Grep, Make et Texinfo</seg></seglistitem>
</segmentedlist>
</sect2>

<sect2 role="installation">
<title>Installation de Sed</title>

<para>Par défaut, Sed installe sa documentation HTML dans
<filename class="directory">/usr/share/doc</filename>. Modifiez ceci par
<filename class="directory">/usr/share/doc/sed-&sed-version;</filename> en
exécutant la commande <command>sed</command> suivante&nbsp;:</para>

<screen><userinput>sed -i 's@/doc@&amp;/sed-&sed-version;@' doc/Makefile.in</userinput></screen>

<para>Préparez la compilation de Sed&nbsp;:</para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr --bindir=/bin</userinput></screen>

<para>Compilez le paquet&nbsp;:</para>

<screen><userinput>make</userinput></screen>

<para>Pour tester les résultats, lancez&nbsp;:
<userinput>make check</userinput>.</para>

<para>Installez le paquet:</para>

<screen><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

</sect2>

